<D>__{it is crowding up. let's get out of here.}
<A>__{they rise. sheldrake leaves some money on the table, leads fran toward the entrance. as they pass miss olsen's booth, she turns around slowly, and putting on her glasses, looks after them. sheldrake slips a bill to the piano player, who gives them a big smile, slides into jealous lover again. retrieving his hat and coat from the checkroom girl, sheldrake steers fran through the door. miss olsen watches them with a cold smile.}
